===Etymology===
Spanish ''[[mandarín]]'' and Portuguese ''[[mandarim]]'', ''[[mandarij]]'', from Malay ''[[menteri]]'', ''[[manteri]]'', from Hindi ''mantri'', from Sanskrit ''[[मन्त्रिन्]]'' (mantrin), "minister", "councillor", from [[मन्त्र]] (mantra) "counsel", "maxim", "mantra" + [[-इन्]] (in), an agent suffix.

